        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 7:34PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 733 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 8 miles northwest of Perryton to near Spearman.
Movement was southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Spearman, Waka, Perryton, and Farnsworth.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
